claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table labeled Table 4 presenting vaccine effectiveness (VE, % [95% CI]) of recombinant quadrivalent influenza vaccine (RIV4), standard dose quadrivalent influenza vaccine (SD-IIV4), RIV4 + high dose IIV4 + adjuvanted IIV (Adj-IV), and SD-IIV4, compared to no vaccination, stratified by age groups (18–64 years and ≥65 years). VE values and confidence intervals are shown for overall populations and females. The table provides vaccine effectiveness data but contains no information on antigenic match or strain selection relative to WHO or FDA recommendations, so it does not support the claim.
